event,"so yesterday, i got bored around 12 am, and decided to go thru the closet and i found some trucker books. they weren't like huge or anything, anyway, being bored as i was, i sat down and skimmed thru them. here's one thing i actually read:

""ever heard folks discussing what they read in newspapers? perhaps you, like many others, think that just because you read something in black and white print, it must be true. why? keep in mind that newspaper writers are human like everyone else, and while they strive to do their jobs accurately, they do make mistakes. just because it's in the paper does not make it God's own truth.

plus, you may need to read ""between the lines"" on occasion rather than only reading the surface print. like in the story i came across about a special task assignment issued by a particular county in my area. a major interstate runs through the heart of that county, and as such, the police were doing a weekend crack-down on truckers who tailgate. officers in unmarked cars were going out, spotting these bumper-riders, videotaping them in the act, then sending out marked cars to pull them over for tickets. the videotape would then be used in court as evidence of guilt.

here's the kicker - one participating officer was noted as saying: ""using unmarked cars is an excellent idea since truckers act like perfect angels when marked cars are around."" hmmm... that may be true, but hello? who doesn't abide by every rule while a cop is around?! i hardly think that bit of common sense is limited to truckers. after all, ever see anyone driving along an interstate, passing a cop doing 20mph faster than he is? might as well wave a flag out the window that says ""hey, look ate me - i'm speeding."" rather, you find a traffic jam of folks 100 feet behind him, afraid to even get close, much less go any faster""

there was more to that. but it was pointless to add it in. anyway, i so agree with the writer, who wouldn't be a perfect little angel on the road when they know a cops around? lol. another thing that caught my attention was this recipe for chili (for all them hardcore cowboys out there =P):
midnight cowyboy's award winning deep south texas chili""
1 big skillet and 1 large pot with lid
5 cans del monte mexican stewed tomatoes
(puree 3 cans in blender and leave 2 cans tomatoes as is)
2 big dashes pickapeppa jamaican sauce (available at all leading supermarkets)
2 big dashes A-1 bold (hot and spicy writeen on label)
in the skillet, brown ground chuck with chopped onion and salt and pepper and garlic powder
column2: drain. in large pot, mix all ingredients listed above and then pour in ground chuck. place lid on pot and heat over a small flame for at least two hours, stirring mixture regularly.

column1: as with any authentic chili makers, use your own ideas in adding tasteful items to this basic recipe. suggested SIDE DISHES to use with prepared chili include chopped onion, chopped jalapeno peppers, and/or grated cheese.
so those 2 things were about all i was interested in from those trucker books. anyway, wrote a little poem:
tired of searching for that one special guy
the one who's supposedly right for me
im tired of wondering what he's like
is he mean or is he nice?
when is he gonna come into my life
is he white, black, mexican ore asian?
so i can find this guy now
i need to know who he is
and see if he's right for this little chick
i'll find the man of my dreams
ima find by the end of this day
so i can stop wondering who he is
and finally meet the perfect guy for me

so yes, that' my little poem. and to answer those who actually read this whole entire post form beginning to end, yes.. i was/am that bored. but you must be even more bored to have had read this whole thing. =P and btw, im not done yet. keep reading! lol. just revently found out my brother says ""dude"" not that it's a crime or anything, but it sounds funny coming from him. and plus, i used to say it (but i don't anymore cuz i don't like to say it, but i don't care if you say it i just don't like to say it =P) anyway, so i used to say it, and he used to be a hater and bug the crap out of me when i said it.. so should i do the same to him? i mean what goes around comes around right? lol. naw, im not that mean. =P 19 days and school will be back in session.. so who's ready for school? im not. =P i haven't even read my summer reading yet.. i didn't even buy it yet. .. bleh .. i don't like reading.. i guess that's all for now.. im done. hehe. i seriously doubt anyone read this entire thing from start to finish.. but w/e, who am i to force you guys to read something against your will? and i myself, one who dislikes reading. =P well i love you guys anyway even if you didn't read this.
